Opening the website Using XAMPP:

Download and Install XAMPP:

Visit the XAMPP official website and download the appropriate version for your operating system.
Run the installer and follow the installation instructions.
Start Apache and MySQL:

Open the XAMPP Control Panel.
Click the "Start" button next to Apache and MySQL to start these services. Ensure both services are running (indicated by green highlights).
Place Your Website Files:

Navigate to the XAMPP installation directory (usually C:\xampp on Windows).
Open the htdocs folder.
Copy your website files into the htdocs folder. You can create a subfolder within htdocs to keep your files organized (e.g., C:\xampp\htdocs\sportstxt).
Access Your Website:

Open a web browser.
Type http://localhost or http://localhost/sportstxt if you created a subfolder.
Press Enter. Your website should now be accessible.